&lt;p&gt;I saw a lot of beautiful hydrangeas in the sacred place Mt.Yoshino.&lt;br&gt;
Every clusters were so big and filled with energy. I felt this was reality. My eyes opened. I’d like to keep it in my mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this year, I’m interested in reading postmodern books more.&lt;br&gt;
Especially literature, philosophy and criticism spark my curiosity. Active authors provide me with inspiration and guidance. I receive divine afflatus through them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For instance…  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;鏡の中を数える (Counting the Inside of a Mirror) by Prabda Yoon
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.typhoonbooksjapan.com/e/catalogue/kagami_no_naka.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.typhoonbooksjapan.com/e/catalogue/kagami&lt;em&gt;no&lt;/em&gt;naka.html&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ゲンロン (Genron) by Hiroki Azuma(ed.), et al&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://genron-tomonokai.com/genron/en/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://genron-tomonokai.com/genron/en/&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These books teach me a possible next step in the future. The step is not too emotional. And it’s not too logical. It’s cool as a cucumber and so kind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I like things I can feel a ray of sunshine.&lt;br&gt;
All experiences are very good openers to open my eyes.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>